Fix: address code review comments on STSAssumeRoleToken PR

Three changes:

1. AGENTS.md parenthesis fix — cosmetic, no behavioral impact.

2. AGENTS.md Expected Flow hardening — added explicit gate requiring
   the agent to ask for user confirmation before giving the commit
   command. Previous wording was easy to skip over; new wording has
   a hard stop with a required question.

3. TestRequestParametersApplied — fills a test gap flagged in review:
   the requestParameters test previously only checked output credentials
   (which are mocked and always correct regardless of options). New test
   uses capturingFactory to apply optFns to a real AssumeRoleOptions
   struct and asserts Duration==7200s and ExternalID=="my-external-id"
   are actually forwarded. A regression in option-building logic would
   now be caught.
